Description: Implements the Butterworth-Induced Autoregressive (BTWAR)
    modeling framework, where autoregressive coefficients are derived
    from analog Butterworth filter prototypes mapped to the discrete-
    time domain via the Matched Z-Transform. The approach provides a
    structured link between frequency-domain filter design and
    time-domain autoregressive modeling. Model selection is performed
    using nested rolling-origin cross-validation.
